      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DR. ODIN (1) was never in contention last time after drifting back at this track, but prior to that won by 2.25 lengths at this track (24.01) beating Sweet Trilby in a Rank Limit - Grade 5 on June 15. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Tough to beat if on-song. LUCKY HARPER (6) comes off an average run last start when eighth at Sale over 435m behind Newbrock Tilly (26.45) in a Bottom Up - Grade 5. Placed at his previous run. The form out of his last race has been franked. Key runner on best form. MANDOLIN STORM (7) was among the minors three back at Geelong then missed the frame the last two, but drawn box 7 this time where she has three wins. Well placed here and should do much better. SURGING (2) will run well despite no experience on this track.",
